            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EAs%20used%20in%20this%20context%2C%20your%20neighbor%20means%20%22someone%20near.%22%20God%20has%20positioned%20near%20us%20all%20kinds%20of%20people%20with%20all%20kinds%20of%20needs.%20By%20showing%20love%20and%20generosity%20to%20such%20people%2C%20we%20are%20fulfilling%20one%20of%20the%20greatest%20commandments.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20children%20of%20Israel%20were%20told%20to%20treat%20a%20runaway%20slave%20as%20a%20neighbor%20and%20to%20give%20him%20refuge%20(Deuteronomy%2023%3A15).%20They%20were%20also%20told%20not%20to%20barge%20into%20a%20neighbor's%20house%20to%20take%20an%20article%20for%20collateral.%20They%20were%20to%20let%20the%20person%20bring%20it%20out%20to%20them%2C%20and%20if%20the%20neighbor%20was%20poor%20and%20had%20only%20a%20cloak%20for%20collateral%2C%20they%20could%20not%20keep%20it%20overnight.%20In%20addition%2C%20they%20were%20told%20to%20leave%20intentional%20harvests%20of%20wheat%2C%20olives%2C%20and%20grapes%20for%20the%20poor%20(Deuteronomy%2024%3A10-13%2C19-21).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20generosity%20of%20the%20Good%20Samaritan%20to%20his%20%22neighbor%2C%22%20someone%20who%20was%20near%2C%20distinguished%20his%20true%20religion%20from%20the%20selfish%20religion%20of%20the%20Levite%20and%20priest%20(Luke%2010%3A25-35).%20Likewise%2C%20Jesus'%20commandment%20to%20us%20is%20%22Now%20go%20and%20do%20the%20same%22%20(v.%2037).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWe%20complicate%20our%20religion%20when%20we%20think%20of%20it%20as%20distant%20and%20difficult.%20In%20fact%2C%20it%20is%20near-as%20near%20as%20a%20neighbor%20in%20need.%20If%20we%20focus%20our%20love%20and%20generosity%20on%20neighbors%20in%20need%2C%20God%20will%20meet%20our%20own%20needs%20in%20return.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
