            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Deuteronomy.23:1-25:19",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3EDeuteronomy%2023%3A1-25%3A19%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_23_1%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EDeuteronomy%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3ERegulations%20concerning%20Worship%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E23%3A1%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Verses%2023%3A1-25%20are%20numbered%2023%3A2-26%20in%20Hebrew%20text.%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BIf%20a%20man%26%23x2019%3Bs%20testicles%20are%20crushed%20or%20his%20penis%20is%20cut%20off%2C%20he%20may%20not%20be%20admitted%20to%20the%20assembly%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_23_2%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BIf%20a%20person%20is%20illegitimate%20by%20birth%2C%20neither%20he%20nor%20his%20descendants%20for%20ten%20generations%20may%20be%20admitted%20to%20the%20assembly%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_23_3%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BNo%20Ammonite%20or%20Moabite%20or%20any%20of%20their%20descendants%20for%20ten%20generations%20may%20be%20admitted%20to%20the%20assembly%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_23_4%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EThese%20nations%20did%20not%20welcome%20you%20with%20food%20and%20water%20when%20you%20came%20out%20of%20Egypt.%20Instead%2C%20they%20hired%20Balaam%20son%20of%20Beor%20from%20Pethor%20in%20distant%20Aram-naharaim%20to%20curse%20you.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_23_5%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20your%20God%20refused%20to%20listen%20to%20Balaam.%20He%20turned%20the%20intended%20curse%20into%20a%20blessing%20because%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20your%20God%20loves%20you.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_23_6%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EAs%20long%20as%20you%20live%2C%20you%20must%20never%20promote%20the%20welfare%20and%20prosperity%20of%20the%20Ammonites%20or%20Moabites.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_23_7%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BDo%20not%20detest%20the%20Edomites%20or%20the%20Egyptians%2C%20because%20the%20Edomites%20are%20your%20relatives%20and%20you%20lived%20as%20foreigners%20among%20the%20Egyptians.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_23_8%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20third%20generation%20of%20Edomites%20and%20Egyptians%20may%20enter%20the%20assembly%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_23_9%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EMiscellaneous%20Regulations%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BWhen%20you%20go%20to%20war%20against%20your%20enemies%2C%20be%20sure%20to%20stay%20away%20from%20anything%20that%20is%20impure.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_23_10%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BAny%20man%20who%20becomes%20ceremonially%20defiled%20because%20of%20a%20nocturnal%20emission%20must%20leave%20the%20camp%20and%20stay%20away%20all%20day.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_23_11%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EToward%20evening%20he%20must%20bathe%20himself%2C%20and%20at%20sunset%20he%20may%20return%20to%20the%20camp.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_23_12%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BYou%20must%20have%20a%20designated%20area%20outside%20the%20camp%20where%20you%20can%20go%20to%20relieve%20yourself.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_23_13%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EEach%20of%20you%20must%20have%20a%20spade%20as%20part%20of%20your%20equipment.%20Whenever%20you%20relieve%20yourself%2C%20dig%20a%20hole%20with%20the%20spade%20and%20cover%20the%20excrement.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_23_14%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20camp%20must%20be%20holy%2C%20for%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20your%20God%20moves%20around%20in%20your%20camp%20to%20protect%20you%20and%20to%20defeat%20your%20enemies.%20He%20must%20not%20see%20any%20shameful%20thing%20among%20you%2C%20or%20he%20will%20turn%20away%20from%20you.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_23_15%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BIf%20slaves%20should%20escape%20from%20their%20masters%20and%20take%20refuge%20with%20you%2C%20you%20must%20not%20hand%20them%20over%20to%20their%20masters.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_23_16%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3ELet%20them%20live%20among%20you%20in%20any%20town%20they%20choose%2C%20and%20do%20not%20oppress%20them.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_23_17%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BNo%20Israelite%2C%20whether%20man%20or%20woman%2C%20may%20become%20a%20temple%20prostitute.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_23_18%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20you%20are%20bringing%20an%20offering%20to%20fulfill%20a%20vow%2C%20you%20must%20not%20bring%20to%20the%20house%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20your%20God%20any%20offering%20from%20the%20earnings%20of%20a%20prostitute%2C%20whether%20a%20man%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E23%3A18%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ea%20dog.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20or%20a%20woman%2C%20for%20both%20are%20detestable%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20your%20God.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22deut_23_19%22%20bk%3D%22deut%22%20ch%3D%2223%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BDo%20not%20charge%20interest%20on%20the%20loans%20you%20make%20to%20a%20fellow%20Israelite%2C%20wheth